Class net.sourceforge.cruisecontrol.sourcecontrols.MKS extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

Serialized Fields

properties

SourceControlProperties properties

project

java.lang.String project

localWorkingDir

java.io.File localWorkingDir

doNothing

boolean doNothing
if this attribute is set to true, no mks command is executed. This is for testing purposes, if a potentially slow mks server connection should avoid

listOfModifications

java.util.List listOfModifications
This is the workaround for the missing feature of MKS to return differences for a given time period. If a modification is detected during the quietperiod, CruiseControl calls getModifications of this sourcecontrol object again, with the new values for Date now. In that case, and if all modification are already found in the first cycle, the list of modifications becomes empty. Therefor, we have to return the summarized list of modifications: the values from the last run, and -maybe- results return by MKS for this run.

lastBuild

java.util.Date lastBuild
The listOfModifications is cleared when new value for lastBuild is used.
